;===============================================================================================================
;                                              Captive Descriptions - ADVENT
;===============================================================================================================

[InR_Captive_AdventTrooper X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT Trooper Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT Trooper Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a ADVENT Trooper Captive we have in the Brig. Due to the lack of ADVENT protocols regarding their capture, Troopers often resign themselves to sitting on a corner of the holding cell."

[InR_Captive_AdventStunlancer X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT Stun Lancer Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT Stun Lancer Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a ADVENT Stun Lancer Captive we have in the Brig. Their hyperactive nature clashes with the monotony of the Brig, resulting in them performing all sorts of physical exercises while waiting."

[InR_Captive_AdventPurifier X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT Purifier Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT Purifier Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a ADVENT Purifier Captive we have in the Brig. They frequently display visible discomfort at the cell's relatively cool temperature, and have made several demands to increase it."

[InR_Captive_AdventShieldbearer X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT Shieldbearer Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT Shieldbearer Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a ADVENT Shieldbearer Captive we have in the Brig. They are often seen walking in a slow, calculated stride, likely a conditioned response to their heavy armor."

[InR_Captive_AdventCaptain X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT Captain Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT Captain Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a ADVENT Captain Captive we have in the Brig. They mantain a strict routine, including physical exercise and demanding punctuality for the service of meals."

[InR_Captive_AdventPriest X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT Priest Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT Priest Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a ADVENT Priest Captive we have in the Brig. Most of their time is spent in a kneeling position, and can be heard begging forgiveness from the Elders."

[InR_Captive_AdventGeneral X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT General Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT General Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a ADVENT General Captive we have in the Brig. They seem to suffer from constant headaches, a probable consequence of the loss of the psionic flow in their command chip."

;===============================================================================================================
;                                              Captive Descriptions - Alien
;===============================================================================================================

[InR_Captive_Andromedon X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Andromedon Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Andromedon Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Andromedon Captive we have in the Brig. A stasis mechanism we installed on their suit allows us to safely interact and clean the cell of the suit's corrosive byproducts."

[InR_Captive_Archon X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Archon Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Archon Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Archon Captive we have in the Brig. While they spend most of their time in a state of relative inactivity, random bursts of anger and violence are common in our Archon captives."

[InR_Captive_Berserker X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Berserker Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Berserker Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Berserker Captive we have in the Brig. Due to the heavy amount of sedatives we employ, Berserkers are often seen calmly sleeping in their cell."

[InR_Captive_Chryssalid X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Chryssalid Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Chryssalid Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Chryssalid Captive we have in the Brig. It constantly moves in the cell, as if experiencing great anxiety due to the confined environment."

[InR_Captive_Faceless X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Faceless Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Faceless Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Faceless Captive we have in the Brig. Constant attempts at impersonating XCOM personnel in order to get free have forced us to adopt tight surveillance measures."

[InR_Captive_Muton X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Muton Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Muton Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Muton Captive we have in the Brig. They are often seen performing complex chants and rituals of yet-undetermined purpose, but otherwise mantain remarkable composure in captivity."

[InR_Captive_Sectoid X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Sectoid Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Sectoid Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Sectoid Captive we have in the Brig. They have demonstrated remarkable compliance with our instructions, although they seem to be somewhat unfamiliar at communication without relying on psionics."

[InR_Captive_Viper X2ItemTemplate]
FriendlyName="Viper Captive"
FriendlyNamePlural="Viper Captives"
BriefSummary="This is a Viper Captive we have in the Brig. They have proved to be very talkative, and alternate between sarcastic insults, threats and attempts to negotiate their release."

